'''''Coutarea''''' is a [[genus]] of [[flowering plant]]s in the family [[Rubiaceae]].<ref>[https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/page/362290#page/348/mode/1up Aublet, Jean Baptiste Christophe Fusée. 1775.  Histoire des Plantes de la Guiane Françoise 1: 314, t. 122]</ref> The genus is native to southern [[Mexico]], [[Central America]], [[South America]] and the [[West Indies]].<ref>[http://apps.kew.org/wcsp/namedetail.do?name_id=48562 Kew World Checklist of Selected Plant Families, ''Coutarea'']</ref>

These plants are woody trees and shrubs with oppositely arranged leaves and terminal inflorescences. The large, showy flowers are white, pink, red, or purplish, sometimes with whitish or greenish markings. The fruit is a woody, flattened capsule containing seeds with large wings.<ref name=trop>[http://www.tropicos.org/Name/40015606?projectid=34 ''Coutarea''.] Selected Rubiaceae Tribes and Genera. Tropicos.</ref>

==Species==
*''[[Coutarea andrei]]'' <small>[[Paul Carpenter Standley|Standl.]]</small> - [[Ecuador]], [[Peru]]
*''[[Coutarea coutaportloides]]'' <small>C.M.Taylor</small> - Ecuador
*''[[Coutarea diervilloides]]'' <small>[[Jules Émile Planchon|Planch.]] & Linden</small> - [[Colombia]]
*''[[Coutarea fuchsioides]]'' <small>C.M.Taylor</small> - Peru
*''[[Coutarea hexandra]]'' <small>([[Nikolaus Joseph von Jacquin|Jacq.]]) [[Karl Moritz Schumann|K.Schum.]]</small> - widespread in Latin America
*''[[Coutarea mollis]]'' <small>[[Adelbert von Chamisso|Cham.]]</small> - [[Brazil]]

